Jenkins - Continuos Integration tool
----------------------
Pre-requisites:
----
1) Download install jenkins
	1st method( permanant/stand alone installation)-(Through Installer)
		Download Jenkins:  https://www.jenkins.io/download/
		you will get jenkins.msi file
		After installation URL: http://localhost:8080/

	2nd method(whenever you want o work with jenkins you can launch it direclty)
		Download .war file and keep it in C:\jenkins  folder

		After running the war file in command prompt then open URL: http://localhost:8080/

2) Create environment varialbes(applicable for both the methods)
	Right click on MyPC--> Properties-->Adv System settings-->Env variables--<New button under system varaible
	JAVA_HOME
	M2_HOME
	MAVEN_HOME

	Select path varialbe --> Edit--New
		%JAVA_HOME%bin
		%MAVEN_HOME%bin
		%M2_HOME%bin
	add git path  : C:\Program Files\Git\bin\

3) Launch Jenkins using .war file
	open the command prompt
	Navigate to location	

	java -jar jenkins.war


4) Do first time configurations in jenkins tool( follow the document)